<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<title>Compliance Freeze Request — Case {{ case_id }}</title>
{% include "_styles.html.j2" %}
</head>
<body>

<section class="cover">
  <div class="cover-letterhead">
    <div class="cover-wordmark">
      Recupero
      <span class="tagline">Investigation Services</span>
    </div>
    <div class="cover-letterhead-right">
      <div class="confidential">Strictly Private &amp; Confidential</div>
      <div class="date">{{ generated_at }} UTC</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="cover-title-block">
    <div class="cover-eyebrow">Time-Sensitive Compliance Matter</div>
    <h1>Compliance<br/>Freeze Request</h1>
    <p class="cover-subtitle">
      A stolen {{ asset.symbol }} position is currently held in an
      identifiable wallet under {{ issuer.short_name }}'s issuance
      authority. We respectfully request a voluntary precautionary
      freeze pending law-enforcement engagement.
    </p>
    <div class="cover-rule"></div>
  </div>

  <dl class="cover-meta">
    <div class="cover-meta-item">
      <dt>Addressed To</dt>
      <dd>{{ issuer.name }}<span class="secondary">Compliance &amp; Security<br/>{{ issuer.contact_email }}</span></dd>
    </div>
    <div class="cover-meta-item">
      <dt>Prepared By</dt>
      <dd>{{ investigator.name }}<span class="secondary">{{ investigator.organization }}<br/>on behalf of {{ victim.name }}</span></dd>
    </div>
    <div class="cover-meta-item">
      <dt>Case Number</dt>
      <dd>{{ case_id }}</dd>
    </div>
    <div class="cover-meta-item">
      <dt>Brief Identifier</dt>
      <dd class="mono">{{ brief_id }}</dd>
    </div>
    <div class="cover-meta-item">
      <dt>Stolen Asset</dt>
      <dd>{{ asset.symbol }}<span class="secondary mono">{{ asset.contract }}</span></dd>
    </div>
    <div class="cover-meta-item">
      <dt>Initial Value</dt>
      <dd>USD {{ asset.usd_value_at_theft }}</dd>
    </div>
  </dl>
</section>

<div class="summary-box urgent">
  <p style="margin:0"><strong>Summary.</strong>
    On {{ theft_event.timestamp_human }} UTC, the Ethereum wallet of
    {{ victim.name }} ({{ victim.wallet_address }}) was drained of
    <strong>{{ asset.amount_human }} {{ asset.symbol }}</strong>
    (initial value: <strong>USD {{ asset.usd_value_at_theft }}</strong>).
    The asset is a {{ asset.description }}.
    The stolen position was forwarded by the perpetrator within hours to wallet
    <span class="mono">{{ current_holder.address }}</span>, where on-chain records
    show <strong>it currently remains intact</strong>
    (last verified {{ verified_at }} UTC; {{ outbound_count_of_stolen_asset }} outbound
    transfers of this specific asset observed since receipt).
    We respectfully request that {{ issuer.short_name }} voluntarily freeze redemption
    rights on this specific position pending engagement with law enforcement
    authorities representing the victim.
  </p>
</div>

<h2>1. Victim Identification</h2>
<dl class="meta-grid">
  <dt>Name:</dt>            <dd>{{ victim.name }}</dd>
  {% if victim.citizenship %}<dt>Citizenship:</dt><dd>{{ victim.citizenship }}</dd>{% endif %}
  {% if victim.address %}<dt>Address:</dt><dd>{{ victim.address }}</dd>{% endif %}
  {% if victim.email %}<dt>Email:</dt>      <dd>{{ victim.email }}</dd>{% endif %}
  {% if victim.phone %}<dt>Phone:</dt>      <dd>{{ victim.phone }}</dd>{% endif %}
  <dt>Affected wallet:</dt> <dd>{{ victim.wallet_address }}</dd>
  {% if victim.legal_counsel %}
  <dt>Legal counsel:</dt><dd>{{ victim.legal_counsel }}{% if victim.legal_counsel_email %} &lt;{{ victim.legal_counsel_email }}&gt;{% endif %}</dd>
  {% endif %}
</dl>

{% if victim.incident_summary %}
<p>{{ victim.incident_summary }}</p>
{% endif %}

{% if issuer.kyc_required %}
<div class="summary-box action">
  <p style="margin:0"><strong>KYC Holder Verification.</strong>
    Acquisition of {{ asset.symbol }} requires {{ issuer.short_name }}-administered
    KYC verification{% if issuer.kyc_minimum %} with a minimum subscription of
    {{ issuer.kyc_minimum }}{% endif %}. {{ victim.name }} is an established
    {{ asset.symbol }} holder and would have completed {{ issuer.short_name }}'s KYC
    process at the time of original deposit. We respectfully suggest that
    {{ issuer.short_name }}'s internal records will confirm {{ victim.name }} as the
    legitimate KYC'd holder of the affected position. By contrast, the wallet
    <span class="mono">{{ current_holder.address }}</span> currently holding the
    stolen position has no record of completing {{ issuer.short_name }} KYC — it is
    a freshly-created wallet that received the position by direct on-chain transfer
    only. This asymmetry strengthens the basis for a precautionary hold pending
    law-enforcement validation.
  </p>
</div>
{% endif %}

<h2>2. Theft Event</h2>
<table class="evidence">
  <tr><th>Date / time (UTC)</th><td class="mono">{{ theft_event.timestamp_human }}</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Block</th>             <td class="mono">{{ theft_event.block_number }}</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Transaction hash</th>  <td class="mono"><a href="{{ theft_event.explorer_url }}">{{ theft_event.tx_hash }}</a></td></tr>
  <tr><th>From (victim)</th>     <td class="mono victim-row">{{ theft_event.from_address }}</td></tr>
  <tr><th>To (perpetrator)</th>  <td class="mono perp-row">{{ theft_event.to_address }}</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Asset</th>             <td>{{ asset.symbol }} <span class="small">(contract: <span class="mono">{{ asset.contract }}</span>)</span></td></tr>
  <tr><th>Amount</th>            <td class="amount">{{ asset.amount_human }} {{ asset.symbol }}</td></tr>
  <tr><th>USD value at time of transaction</th><td class="amount">USD {{ asset.usd_value_at_theft }}</td></tr>
  {% if asset.usd_value_current %}
  <tr><th>USD value (current estimate)</th>    <td class="amount">USD {{ asset.usd_value_current }}</td></tr>
  {% endif %}
</table>

<h2>3. Forwarding Chain (perpetrator's movements)</h2>
{% if hops %}
<p>After the theft, the funds moved through the following wallets controlled by the perpetrator:</p>
<table class="evidence">
  <tr>
    <th>Hop</th><th>Date (UTC)</th><th>Tx hash</th>
    <th>From</th><th>To</th><th>Amount</th>
  </tr>
  {% for hop in hops %}
  <tr>
    <td>{{ loop.index }}</td>
    <td class="mono">{{ hop.timestamp_human }}</td>
    <td class="mono"><a href="{{ hop.explorer_url }}">{{ hop.tx_hash[:14] }}…</a></td>
    <td class="mono perp-row">{{ hop.from_address }}</td>
    <td class="mono perp-row">{{ hop.to_address }}</td>
    <td class="amount">{{ hop.amount_human }} {{ hop.symbol }}</td>
  </tr>
  {% endfor %}
</table>
{% else %}
<p>No subsequent forwarding observed; the funds remain in the perpetrator's initial receiving wallet.</p>
{% endif %}

{% if flow_svg %}
<h3>Fund flow visualization</h3>
<div class="flow-diagram" data-case="{{ case_id }}">
  {{ flow_svg|safe }}
  <div class="flow-caption">
    Visualization of observed on-chain transfers from victim wallet
    through to current location of the stolen position. Edge labels
    show USD-denominated value at time of transfer.
    <div class="flow-legend">
      <span class="swatch victim">Victim wallet</span>
      <span class="swatch exchange">Labeled exchange</span>
      <span class="swatch mixer">Mixer</span>
      <span class="swatch bridge">Bridge</span>
      <span class="swatch wallet">Unlabeled wallet</span>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
{% endif %}

<h2>4. Current Location of Stolen Position</h2>
<div class="summary-box action">
  <p style="margin:0"><strong>The {{ asset.amount_human }} {{ asset.symbol }} position is currently held in:</strong></p>
  <p class="mono" style="font-size:11pt; margin:0.5em 0;">{{ current_holder.address }}</p>
  <p style="margin:0">
    <a href="{{ current_holder.explorer_url }}">View on Etherscan</a>
    &nbsp;·&nbsp;
    <a href="{{ current_holder.explorer_url }}#tokentxns">Token transfer history</a>
  </p>
  <p style="margin:0.5em 0 0;">
    <strong>Last verified:</strong> {{ verified_at }} UTC.
    <strong>Outbound transfers of this asset observed:</strong> {{ outbound_count_of_stolen_asset }}.
  </p>
</div>

<h2>5. Specific Request</h2>
<p>
  We respectfully request that {{ issuer.name }} take the following actions:
</p>
<ol>
  <li>
    <strong>Voluntarily place a hold on redemption rights</strong> for the
    {{ asset.amount_human }} {{ asset.symbol }} position currently held in
    <span class="mono">{{ current_holder.address }}</span>,
    pending engagement with law enforcement authorities representing the victim.
  </li>
  <li>
    <strong>Confirm receipt of this request</strong> in writing, noting the date and time
    {{ issuer.short_name }} was placed on notice of the alleged theft.
  </li>
  <li>
    <strong>Designate a point of contact</strong> for follow-up coordination with
    law enforcement. We anticipate a formal request from the relevant authorities
    (French national police / EU cooperation channels) to follow.
  </li>
  {% if issuer.kyc_required %}
  <li>
    <strong>Confirm via internal records</strong> whether {{ victim.name }} is registered
    as the original KYC'd subscriber for the affected position. This information is
    needed solely to corroborate ownership and would not need to be shared externally.
  </li>
  {% endif %}
</ol>
<p>
  We recognize that {{ issuer.name }} is not a party to the underlying theft and are
  not asserting any wrongdoing on {{ issuer.short_name }}'s part. This request is
  made because {{ issuer.short_name }}'s protocol-level controls represent the most
  rapid available means of preventing further dissipation of the stolen funds
  while law enforcement procedures are initiated.
</p>

{% if issuer.regulatory_framework %}
<h2>6. Applicable Regulatory Context</h2>
<p>
  {{ issuer.name }} operates under {{ issuer.regulatory_framework }}.
  {% if victim.citizenship %}
  The victim, {{ victim.name }}, is a citizen of {{ victim.citizenship }}, an EU
  member state. This case therefore falls within established EU cross-border
  regulatory cooperation frameworks for the protection of consumer/investor interests
  in tokenized assets.
  {% endif %}
</p>
{% endif %}

<h2>7. Independent Verification</h2>
<p>
  All facts in this brief are derived from public Ethereum mainnet data and are
  independently verifiable. Each transaction hash above links to its Etherscan
  record. The on-chain state of <span class="mono">{{ current_holder.address }}</span>
  as of {{ verified_at }} UTC shows {{ outbound_count_of_stolen_asset }} outbound
  transfers of {{ asset.symbol }} from that wallet to date.
</p>
<p class="small">
  Data sources: Etherscan API v2 (Ethereum mainnet transaction history),
  CoinGecko (historical USD valuation), {{ investigator.organization }} cross-case
  entity attribution database.
</p>

<h2>8. Contact</h2>
<table class="evidence">
  <tr><th>Investigator</th><td><strong>{{ investigator.name }}</strong></td></tr>
  <tr><th>Organization</th><td>{{ investigator.organization }}</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Email</th><td><a href="mailto:{{ investigator.email }}">{{ investigator.email }}</a></td></tr>
  {% if investigator.phone %}<tr><th>Phone</th><td>{{ investigator.phone }}</td></tr>{% endif %}
  <tr><th>Reply expected</th><td>Acknowledgement within 24 hours; substantive response within 72 hours</td></tr>
</table>

<footer class="brief-footer">
  <div class="footer-brand">Recupero · Investigation Services</div>
  <div class="footer-meta">
    <code>{{ brief_id }}</code><br/>
    Generated {{ generated_at }} UTC · v{{ software_version }}<br/>
    <span class="confidential">Strictly Confidential.</span> Intended only for recipient compliance review.
  </div>
</footer>

</body>
</html>
